  <prompt>
    Extend `AnalysisChunk` (the canonical SSE envelope for BFF AI streaming output) with a
    new additive `FieldDelta` variant. The variant introduces a single new event type
    (`Type = "delta"`) and a new `FieldDelta` record (`Path`, `Content`, `Sequence`) that
    will carry JSON-path-tagged token chunks for structured-field streaming. This is the
    SSE-side primitive R5's "Summarize a Document" vertical slice relies on for ChatGPT-style
    progressive rendering in `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (D2-07) and is consumed by the
    incremental JSON parser in D1-06 (which depends on this task).

    **Critical-path significance**: This task is item #2 on the R5 critical path
    (`001 â†’ 005 â†’ 006 â†’ 010 â†’ 012 â†’ 014 â†’ 017 â†’ 020 â†’ 031 â†’ 040 â†’ 043 â†’ 044 â†’ 090`).
    Task 006 (D1-06) â€” switching Summarize playbook execution to Azure OpenAI Structured
    Outputs + incremental JSON parser â€” cannot start until this variant lands.

    **Strict additive contract** (R5 reuse mandate Â§3.1 â€” "Specifically prohibited"):
    R5 MUST NOT introduce a parallel SSE envelope. R5 EXTENDS `AnalysisChunk` with a new
    nullable `Delta` property and a new discriminant value (`"delta"`); ALL existing
    properties, serialization shapes, factory methods, and consumer behaviour are
    preserved. Existing wizard consumers â€” specifically
    `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/summarizeService.ts`
    `streamSummarize()` â€” already filter on known discriminants (`progress`/`result`/
    `error`/`done`); the new `"delta"` event will be silently ignored by them, which is
    the back-compat contract per NFR-10.

    R5 is configuration-first: this task ships a model edit + serialization tests + a
    documented back-compat verification. No DI changes. No endpoint changes. BFF
    publish-size delta MUST be measured and reported per CLAUDE.md Â§10 / R5 Â§3.6
    (target â‰ˆ 0 MB; ceiling â‰¤ +0.5 MB single-task).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer with deep familiarity with `System.Text.Json` source-gen + record
    types, additive contract evolution, and SSE event-stream protocols. Comfortable
    reasoning about back-compat of polymorphic-by-discriminant envelopes and writing
    serialization round-trip + consumer-behaviour tests.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `AnalysisChunk` exposes a new additive `FieldDelta` variant: a new `Delta` property of
    type `FieldDelta?` (nullable, JSON-serialized as `"delta"` when present and omitted
    when null), a new `FieldDelta` record (`Path`, `Content`, `Sequence`), and a new
    factory `AnalysisChunk.FromDelta(path, content, sequence)` that produces an instance
    with `Type = "delta"`, `Done = false`, and the `Delta` property set. The record
    compiles, round-trips through `JsonSerializer.Serialize` + `JsonSerializer.Deserialize`
    with no data loss, and a wizard-consumer parity test confirms that existing
    `streamSummarize()`-style parsing logic (filtering on known discriminants) treats
    `"delta"` events as no-ops without breaking the stream. BFF publish-size delta is
    measured and reported. All acceptance criteria below are green.
  </goal>

