  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 reuse mandate (CLAUDE.md Â§3.1 â€” Specifically prohibited)">MUST EXTEND `AnalysisChunk` with the new `FieldDelta` variant. MUST NOT introduce a parallel SSE envelope, a new chunk type alongside `AnalysisChunk`, or a duplicate `FieldDelta`-bearing record. The new variant is an additive property + a new discriminant value on the existing envelope.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-10 (back-compat)">Existing wizard consumers (LegalWorkspace `SummarizeFilesDialog` via `streamSummarize()`) MUST continue to function unchanged. Existing discriminant values (`text`, `progress`, `result`, `complete`, `error`) and their serialization shapes MUST round-trip byte-identically before and after this change. New consumers ignore the `"delta"` discriminant by default.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-02">The `FieldDelta` record carries `Path` (JSON path, e.g., `"tldr"`, `"fileHighlights[0].summary"`), `Content` (token chunk for the field), and `Sequence` (int â€” ordering correctness if deltas are reordered downstream).</constraint>
    <constraint source="design Â§4.3">`AnalysisChunk` gains a `FieldDelta? Delta` property (nullable). When `Delta` is null the JSON property MUST be omitted (use `JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull`) so existing serialized payloads are byte-identical. New event type discriminant: `"delta"`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 Â§3.2 (no new feature flags per ADR-018)">No new feature flag introduced by this task. The new variant is unconditional on the model side; downstream emitters (D1-06 Structured Outputs path) emit `"delta"` events only when that code path runs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010 / R5 Â§3.3">No new DI registrations. No new top-level `Program.cs` lines. This task edits a single model file plus tests.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013 / R5 Â§3.5">`AnalysisChunk` lives in `Sprk.Bff.Api.Models.Ai`. No new injection of AI-internal types into CRUD code. No facade boundary impact.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029 / R5 Â§3.6 / CLAUDE.md Â§10">BFF publish-size MUST be measured. Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`, measure compressed output, and record absolute size + delta vs prior baseline (~45.65 MB) in task notes. Target â‰ˆ 0 MB delta; ceiling â‰¤ +0.5 MB single-task; HARD STOP at 60 MB absolute.</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md">Single-file model edit; no new endpoints, no new services, no new packages. Placement justification: trivial â€” `AnalysisChunk` already lives in `Sprk.Bff.Api.Models.Ai`; the new variant + record sit alongside it.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md Â§10 F-test-update / R5 Â§3.7">PRs modifying `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` MUST add/update tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. New tests REQUIRED for: (a) `FromDelta` factory; (b) serialization round-trip for delta and for non-delta variants; (c) `Delta = null` produces no `delta` JSON property (existing-payload byte-identity); (d) wizard-consumer parity (a representative `streamSummarize()`-style parser ignores the `"delta"` discriminant and continues to function).</constraint>
    <constraint source="design Â§4.3">`FieldDelta` semantics: `Path` is a JSON-pointer-style or dotted/array-indexed path identifying which field in the streaming JSON the chunk belongs to (e.g., `tldr`, `fileHighlights[0].summary`). The model does NOT validate the path syntax â€” that is the producer (D1-06 incremental parser) + consumer (D2-07 widget) contract. `Sequence` is a monotonic int from the producer.</constraint>
  </constraints>

